aneously acquire T1 maps for five slices of a human\nbrain ($0.75 \\times 0.75 \\times 5$ mm$^3$) or three slices of the abdomen\n($1.25 \\times 1.25 \\times 6$ mm$^3$) within four seconds. Conclusion: The IR\nSMS radial FLASH acquisition together with a non-linear model-based\nreconstruction enable rapid high-resolution multi-slice T1 mapping with good\naccuracy, precision, and repeatability.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Sep 2019 21:57:41 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 25 Mar 2020 13:47:45 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 17 Jun 2020 06:27:25 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 3 Aug 2020 20:54:13 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 19 Aug 2020 07:34:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-11"}
