e boundaries with cosmic time that\ncause galaxies to quench. BH-scaling laws for star-forming, quenched, and\ngreen-valley galaxies are different, and most BH mass growth takes place in the\ngreen valley. Implications include: the radii of star-forming galaxies are an\nimportant second parameter in shaping their black holes; black holes are\nconnected to their halos but in different ways for star-forming, quenched, and\ngreen-valley galaxies; and the same BH-halo quenching mechanism has been in\nplace since $z \\sim 3$. We conclude with a discussion of black hole-galaxy\nco-evolution, the origin and interpretation of BH scaling laws.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Sep 2019 11:25:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 25 Sep 2019 08:00:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 26 May 2020 09:20:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-15"}
